# Video Consultation Module — Fixes Walkthrough

## Problem Summary
The video consultation system had critical issues: doctor chat messages silently failed due to wrong ID usage, patient endCall had no cleanup, no end-call confirmation dialogs, and the video was stuck on "Connecting."

## Root Cause

The doctor consult page sent `doctorUserId` (auth UUID) as `doctorId` in message API calls, but `messages.doctor_id` references `doctor_profiles.id`. This caused all doctor-sent messages to fail silently.

## Changes Made

### 1. Doctor Consult Page — Complete Rewrite
**File:** [page.tsx](file:///home/surafel/healthapp/app/doctor-dashboard/consult/page.tsx)

- **ID fix**: All message/queue operations now use `doctorProfileId` (resolved from `doctor_profiles`) instead of auth UUID
- **End-call dialog**: Confirmation with two options:
  - "End Consultation" → marks as `completed`, removes from queue
  - "Schedule Follow-up" → marks as `follow_up`, removes from queue
- **Connection status**: Transitions from "Connecting…" to "In consultation — video simulated"
- **Chat file attach**: Added paperclip button in chat input for inline file sharing

---

### 2. Patient Meeting Room — Complete Rewrite
**File:** [MeetingRoom.tsx](file:///home/surafel/healthapp/app/meeting/MeetingRoom.tsx)

- **Proper endCall**: Now updates consultation status to `completed` AND removes from queue
- **End-call dialog**: Confirmation before ending
- **Props**: Accepts `doctorId`, `patientId`, `onEnd` from parent for correct ID usage

---

### 3. Meeting Page — Updated Props
**File:** [page.tsx](file:///home/surafel/healthapp/app/meeting/page.tsx)

- Now passes `doctorId`, `patientId`, `onEnd` to MeetingRoom

---

### 4. Queue API — DELETE Fix
**File:** [route.ts](file:///home/surafel/healthapp/app/api/queue/route.ts)

- DELETE handler now resolves `doctorId` from auth UUID → `doctor_profiles.id` (same as GET)

## Consultation Flow (After Fix)

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    A["Patient joins queue<br/>POST /api/queue"] --> B["Auto-creates consultation"]
    B --> C["Patient in WaitingRoom<br/>Polls position"]
    C --> D["Position 1 → Start Call"]
    D --> E["MeetingRoom: video + chat"]
    E --> F{"End Call?"}
    F -->|"End"| G["PATCH status → completed<br/>DELETE from queue"]
    F -->|"Follow-up"| H["PATCH status → follow_up<br/>DELETE from queue"]
    G --> I["Both dashboards updated"]
    H --> I
```

## Verification
- `npm run build` → **Exit code 0**, zero TypeScript errors
- All routes compiled successfully
